reviews.reviewText: Use your own adhesive. These don't stick for long. There's a reason they come in such large packs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Too-soft, Non-adhesive, Oversized.
reviews.reviewText: The soft silicone material is soft enough to dampen lid and seat drops to a dull thump they they are too soft to support the weight of a person. Ours have fallen into the bowl, been flushed, pulverized, or stuck to unintended articles. They are longer than the standard round seat and twice as long as the bowl rim.

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Does not stick well, though I liked the versatility of having two thicknesses
reviews.reviewText: The adhesive that it comes with does not keep the item in place, so used a super glue. This also, over time, does not hold, and the bumper shifts out of place, needing to be re-glued. I'm sure it has to do with body weight coming down on such a narrow diameter item. It did help keep the toilet seat level after a bidet attachment was put in place.
